review_title: A beautiful soul

review: Cannot play solo - 1 Player is still against another person.

review: For example, if you ask what are side-effects of a medication, it tells you EVERYTHING about it. And if you pause between questions, it repeats the long dialogue from the start.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Lame
review: Doesn't sing the song - Alexa speaks it (poorly)
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good for school - Bad for games
review: Cannot play any games, even old very basic ones. Ok for school, but nothing else.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Fantastic - converts my 10" tablet into a laptop
review: Awesome keyboard with holder for my 10" tablet, and it pairs with my bluetooth mouse as well.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great for my bluetooth keyboard and mouse.
review: I was shopping for the most compact keyboard case, and happily found this fantastic pouch. The material is like foam spandex. Snugly holds my bluetooth keyboard, charger, and wireless mouse.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very compact and good design
review: I was surprised how small they are before opening up. Good quality design and look decent.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Look good
review: Lids don't sit well on top - very loose. And quite small solar panels. Cannot be hung up - must sit on surface because lid just sits very loosely on top.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Definitely improves WIFI signal and speed. But lacks 2 important things.
review: What it lacks is a long enough cord to place the WIFI adapter base on top of a shelf. And the base itself is very light plastic that doesn't stand well. The weight of the wire pulls it over. While it is a good wifi adapter, I chose this one over other similar ones specifically for the base, which in the end I found useless because the cord was too short and it was too light to stand up.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Leaks out completely every day or so
review: Very poor design, and leaks out every day or so. It's a real mess of wires and tubes - all too short and difficult to work with. Very big wall wart type power connector - definitely NOT appropriate for outdoor use, so it has to be tucked inside the lighthouse. It LOOKS great and when it runs it is very nice. But at present I need to figure out why it's leaking out. All hoses are snug, so it's obviously a defect - seems to be a leak around the light inside the lighthouse.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Only 12 levels
review: Finished entire game in one sitting. Only 2 holes per level, 6 levela for just 12 holes. And only 1 shot each level, repeated 3x. 36 shots... Disappointing.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: My son really likes it - dual-ring
review: When rung, it makes ringing sound both directions, for a nice double-ring. My son really likes it.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Bright - easy to setup and remove - plenty of patterns
review: Even in daylight it is bright. Plenty of patterns to select from to find that perfect one to suit the need. It's quite impressive to see. Photos don't really do it justice as it appears small in a picture, but is very bright and effective to see first hand.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Cheap ink - worked fine but a bit messy
review: Be careful when you remove the small plastic strip - it covers an open ink hole. I got blue ink all over one hand before I realized it was open ink.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: The best cover.
review: I've purchased several bed mattress covers over the years, and this is the best. It fits very well without wrinkles, the plastic is silent, and there is no gap between plastic and material layers. Fits King size bed perfectly.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Fantastic little fan.
review: Quiet and distributes air exceptionally well. We use it in a big tent and it rapidly cools down an otherwise hot tent.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great price and product
review: For the price, you cannot expect the highest quality. We found defects in the tarp-type tent floor on one end of the tent (about 1-cm gap in tarp that would allow water in). Also, the door does not open and close as advertised. It doesn't stay closed (velcro does not match up well), unless zippered closed.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Dangerous to use because the basket moves a lot on the pan when placing in or removing from oven.
review:
My real concern is with the basket - it really moves around when you try to handle the pan. There is nothing to keep the basket in place while on the pan. When I open the oven and place it in or try to take it out, the basket moves a lot - slides around about 2 inches back and forth and could easily spill. It's also very, very thin and I don't expect it to last long due to being so flimsy.

On the positive side, it makes everything crispy, and it's very easy to clean up.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: No eyes. Just a weird smile.
review: As you can see, there are no eyes, only small shapes at the end of the mouth. It looks weird - needs eyes.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: They look nice. Sadly not many colour options to choose from.
review: They do look nice, however were not available in the colours we'd prefer. Also, they fit quite tight, even for a small wrist. They may restrict circulation on a larger wrist, and likely on an ankle.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: They are adhesive, but did nothing more than the felt I replaced in reducing noise of cupboard doors
review: They are very expensive. Plus side, they are adhesive. Negative side, they did nothing more than the felt pads I replaced. My cupboard doors still make a bang sound when they close. I even tried doubling and even tripling pads on doors with the same result. In short, they didn't get the results I expected.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Received in 5 business days (during pandemic) - great product
review: Very pleased with the product quality, packaging and shipping. Tested and they work perfectly with HealForce 180B1 (3- lead ECG).
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very good replacement - hope they last
review:
They use a screw to hold the wheel on, which is very good IF they don't rust (are they stainless steel?)
They are sturdy, but also stiff. They do not roll very well at all, but at least they appear to be strong.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: An indoctrination into Protestantism. Makes ONE statement - you get into Heaven by asking for mercy.
review:
This is NOT about Jesus being a rebel. This is NOT about being free from religion. I started reading the 'book' (if you can call it that), and it was just a lot of personal stories strung together awkwardly, with the intention of leading the reader to ONE sole conclusion: There is ONLY ONE way to get to Heaven, and it is to be a Christian and to ask for mercy. But there's a BIG flaw - the author does a lousy job of pretending to be aware of other religions than Protestantism. In an attempt to prop up his own beliefs, he proudly bashes a woman's beliefs in a chapter titled, "ALL RELIGIONS ARE NOT THE SAME".

Wait a second here! Didn't you say this book is about "Breaking Free from Religion to find God"???
What the hypocritical ___?!

He talks about Professors shaming Christians, then he goes on to shame her by LITERALLY bashing Hindu, Buddhism, Atheism (YES even though the book is about BREAKING FREE OF RELIGION). And he goes further to state, "I am a Protestant and not a Catholic because of what the Bible teaches".

Clearly, this isn't a book about Jesus at all. It isn't even a book about being a better person and walking the path of Jesus. It's about ONE MESSAGE which is, if you want to get to Heaven, forget doing good deeds and being a good person, because nobody is perfect and you cannot earn your way in. You must ask for mercy. For all of the good you do, even if almost a saint, you can never be holy - you can never be perfect, and that can only account for 1% of what you need to get into Heaven. The other 99% is asking for mercy. He does his best throughout to HAMMER this home!

He states, "Good people go to Heaven, but there has just never been a good person". So there you have it - his message is not about Jesus being a rebel and walking in His path - his message is, all religion is wrong except for Protestantism, and the ONLY way you can get to Heaven is by 'asking for mercy'.

Question for the author: WHY do you think Jesus provided us with an example of how to live, if it has no bearing on judgement?

Also, I'd like to point out that your statement, "...the way a good Muslim reacts toward a Christian... saying we believe in the same divine Being..." - YES Muslims do believe in the same divine being. AND they have more references to Jesus as 'the Christ' and Messiah (but not the son of God), in the Qu'ran than there are in the Bible. And it says The Christ will return at the end of time for the final judgement. Furthermore, the Catholic Church has an official stand, "The plan of salvation also includes those who acknowledge the Creator, in the first place amongst whom are the Muslims".

All in all, this 'book', is strung-together personal stories that attempt to get across a single message, the ONLY way to Heaven is by asking for mercy. Nothing you do in life, aside from asking for mercy, will get you into Heaven. All religions are wrong, except for Protestantism.

Sadly, I had expected a book that discussed Jesus' examples of standing up for what is right, in the face of opposition. This is how I live my life - making a stand for the weak and innocent, and always suffering the consequences of doing so. I hoped to find strength from Jesus' examples. Sadly, this book is not about that. It's really about nothing other than propping up the author's ego. He believes his way is the right way and the only way, and reading this book feels like getting hit over the head repeatedly by it. One final note, there's no flow to the book. The author's attempt to weave a story fails on all levels. His statements are wrong (and this causes the reader to say, HUH?!), his beliefs are tainted by ego, and he his self-doubt is shown throughout by his need to hammer home his principles.

Advice to author - know your topic. SEEING things is not the same as experiencing them.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great bargain - work perfectly
review: I was surprised to see the quality and packaging. Each individual micro-SD card comes with an SD adapter, and a plastic case. They worked perfectly when installed into 3 tablets and a smartphone. I still have 1 more (of the 5-pack).
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great fun - paired with Origami paper
review: My son is enjoying the instructional book, together with the 100 6" origami sheets. Great combination and lots of fun.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great - paired with Easy Origami book
review: My son is enjoying the paper, together with the book I ordered, Easy Origami. Great combination and lots of fun.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: WARNING! These fit MUCH LARGER than what you think!
review: Ordered a Medium and it is as big as an X-Large. Read other reviews - ALL sizes are much larger than marked. If needing a small, order XXS. If needing a Medium, order an XS - S. VERY big.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Fantastic.
review: This is different from their other book, How to Draw 100 Animals. While all this Covid-19 stuff is going on, I have 4 boys at home. We are enjoying drawing from these books daily.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Cute but my kids have never seen most of these monsters.
review: Well-known monsters are not in this book. It's ok, but could be much better. I'd recommend free images from the internet vs. this book.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Not very good. Most vehicles in the book are fully drawn.
review: The instructions to draw vehicles are quite lacking, and most of the vehicle images are of fully completed drawings. This is pretty useless if looking to draw in steps. I don't recommend this book.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Works great
review: It's quite small so I recommend tying something to it so you can find it easily. Works perfectly with Windows 10, and also with a bootable Linux installation.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great for Linux!
review: Installed full Kubuntu (Linux) (formatted drive), and with little effort got Kubuntu up and running perfectly. I use it with Citrix Receiver and surfing the internet.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: The BEST in match 3 games. Does crash time to time, but no big deal - still the best
review: Of all the match 3 games, these are by far the very best. I purchased 5 of their games so far, and thoroughly enjoy each one. I've play FAR too many hours on each of them. All of them do crash (app has to be restarted) every now and again. But it's no big deal - once you play one of them, you will get more, guaranteed. Very fun to play!
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Lasts 10 hours - exceptional
review: My son really likes these, and is especially pleased that it lasts all day and evening on a single charge.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: It's cute - perfect for my Nurse.
review: It's decent size and looks cute. My wife wears it daily to work.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very good for medical scenarios. Looks pretty realistic with moulage.
review: Durable, and looks pretty realistic.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: CONTACTS forehead. Must sweep temple to temple. Not instant.
review: It IS a good product, but it is misrepresented in the description. It is quite tricky to change from Fahrenheit to Celcius (done with the unit first switched completely off). To do the forehead reading, it requires CONTACT, and sweeps from one temple to the other. This takes a few moments, but is more accurate than a single quick infrared reading. Accuracy is within acceptable range for body temperature. I tried it on several people, and it consistently read our temperatures. Each of us had a different temperature.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Easy to see time and seconds
review: Good watch for nursing or paramedic.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: No better than the mouse I replaced
review: Takes a moment every time to move pointer. Not very comfortable in average size hand. Difficult to click buttons - often takes couple tries to click buttons.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Better than original sprayers
review: Perfect repair kit for my 2007 Durango. Washers are better than new.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great challenge and great design
review: Very advanced Transformer. Detailed, many parts that transform, and really changes completely to a functional toy truck.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: SECURITY WARNING!
review:
Phone uses InPro Comm network interface card (nic) that CONTINUALLY attempts to change its MAC address to connect to wifi network. Over 200x attempts today, each time with a SPOOFED MAC address: 00:08:22:--:--:--
Never uses same MAC address. Screenshots of Disney Cube reveals attempts and random MAC. I t does not stop! Threat warning!
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good looking phone case - decent quality
review: Looks nice. Quality is 4 out of 5 - not exceptionally rugged but looks like it will withstand a drop.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Nice quality and perfect for first aid use.
review: Separate easily. Perfect for rinsing a small wound (first aid).
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Surprisingly EXCELLENT sound quality.
review: Surprisingly exceptional sound from little speaker. It's quite a bit heavier than I expected, and that's good. Sound fills a room - great for presentations.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: TERRIBLE Menu - See screenshot - Can't even select programs to watch (can't scroll down)
review: Menu is absolutely DREADFUL! You are stuck with the pre-configured screen with a huge logos for stuff you don't use. Google Play for example takes up 1/3 of the main menu screen. UNUSABLE menu for 2 of the services I subscribe to: MotorTrend (Velocity), and SNN (Sport Network). Can't see the programs to select to watch. I did everything possible from the terribly designed menu, but still cuts off the program selections. Also, when moving through menus, the selected items are NOT HIGHLIGHTED, so you don't know what you are on. Also, you MUST use mouse mode to select programs with some of the subscribed services, because the direction buttons don't move to some of the menu options.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Hope to never use it. Kept in a first aid kit.
review: Nothing amazing - kept in first aid kit.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Can run SUPER QUIET or reasonably quiet on turbo... many speeds
review: Cleans exceptionally well. You will be surprised what you have been breathing when you see how much has been filtered out of the air with your Honeywell air cleaner. I can't be without it in my bedroom.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great value for the money
review: Nothing really special, but a nice, simple backpack that is very inexpensive.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Eliminate the fear of using an Epipen
review: Every first aid class, or family members who have someone that uses an Epipen, should use a trainer to become familiar with the steps to saving a life.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Handle BENDS when tightening
review: NOT CAT (NOT Combat Application Tourniquet). Handles BEND when tightening to the point they MAY break. You will FEAR they are going to break - as they bend significantly for that last tightening turn. I do NOT recommend these for actual use. If on a tight budget, they are ok for training, but as they will bend, I don't suggest using them at all unless you cannot afford a real CAT/ NAT.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good deal for a hemostatic agent.
review: Must have for any first aid kit. Blood loses its ability to clot within seconds after a bleed starts. So when a wound continues to bleed, this is NECESSARY to stop the bleed.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Quite big. In retrospect, I would have bought a smaller case as this is very big.
review: Nice quality case. Just very big.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: A good deal on a whole-house phone system with answering machine.
review: With voicemail hardly anyone needs an answering machine. But seniors and those who don't care for phone services addons may appreciate it. Good quality - whole-house coverage.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very small. I misread - 3.5" is TOTAL length, not the forceps (clamping part) length.
review: Quality seems fine. These are very small - my mistake for not taking the time to see that I was buying smaller forceps than anticipated.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: The most fun you can bring to any event - bubbles.
review: Loads of fun with this bubble machine - works great. BUT, it's messy. Leaks from the front when angled or tilted in any manner. Also requires some effort to clean after each use, as the soap reservoir is built-in and not removeable. Soap leaks from the reservoir.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very good - can't tell them apart from more expensive ones.
review: They work well. Quality seems good, as we can't tell them apart from more expensive models.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Poor quality plastic.
review: Chipped - even when handled with kitten gloves. I am VERY careful with my remotes to gently place them on the table, kept in my pocket, etc. So no idea how they chip.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Can't say I'm looking forward to trying it out.
review: Very good quality - super compact. Lots of handles, so will work very well as a stretcher.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: EASY to install and looks perfect
review: Looks as good as new after replacing. SUPER easy to install, and now my LG G5 phone camera is as good as new.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good deal. Necessary to replace regularly.
review: Was a better deal than buying locally, and I really had no choice but to buy and replace the pad.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Works SOMETIMES but doesn't eliminate all feedback
review: I expected this to work better. It's too slow to trap feedback frequencies, and does not eliminate all feedback. Honestly, I don't even use it because it's not reliable.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Nice quality blankets.
review: Excellent value for nice quality recycled blankets. They are soft, flexible, and seem durable.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: WORST cable you could EVER buy!
review: Every single cable has FAILED! I gave 2 to my wife for her Samsung phone, 2 to my son for his Samsung phone, and one for my LG G5. EVERY cable FAILED! We pick up our phones and see LOW BATTERY! These cables are absolutely the worst charging cables you could ever buy.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good quality and durable.
review: We use these for belts in medieval costumes. Easy to cut to length. Decent quality - not too thin.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: AWESOME - They really look incredible
review: Used for multicultural dances - look great.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Fantastic costume shoulders
review: These look really great with black or red. Worn with masquerade mask, and we bought some black and red feathers to match these shoulders and glued them on the mask. Really easy to attach - 2x safety pins on each shoulder.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: AWESOME - They really look incredible
review: Worn for part of costume for cultural dancers. Very beautiful and noticeable. The part that goes around the fingertips can be opened up or closed tighter around, for a perfect fit. Very happy with the purchase.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Painful
review: Painful to insert into my ear. Also causes pain when sleeping with them because stem sticks out onto pillow. They may be good for people with big ears, for outdoor type noises. But I'd recommend against using them to sleep.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Perfect solution for charging my 5x 2-way radios
review: 5 ports on one side and 2 on the other. I use this to power 5x 2-way rechargeable radios. It's TINY, so it fits into a pocket on a toolbag that I also keep my radios in. The AC adapter is big, so ensure you have space for it.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Honestly, a waste of money. They only work on dry skin.
review: Most wounds requiring these types of dressing are WET. Lacerations bleed, and most times patients have wet skin. Rendering these steri-strips completely useless. Probably good in a hospital or home-care setting, but not good for first aid.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: We LOVE our tent! Quality is excellent and it is impressive!
review: Everyone comments on how great our tent looks. It's sturdy, durable (we've been using it all summer at events), and looks professional. EXCELLENT deal, especially with the full kit that we got. Sand bags and extra sides for variation depending on weather.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Easy to install new valve.
review: Handy tool worked great. And plenty of spares come with it. I changed the tire valve on a Yamaha Y50 motorcycle.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Matched perfectly - color on screen was what arrived.
review: Son wore this to graduation. Nice quality and matched his date's dress perfectly.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Excellent quality product - impressed.
review: You know what to expect from Littmann Classic III. I use the Littmann Classic II, but my son has a hearing reduction so these are much better for him. You can hear heart and lung sounds much clearer with the III than you can the II.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Too short. Hangs off side of desk.
review: Would be great if the USB 3.0 cable were a little longer The unit hangs off the side of my desk because the cable is too short to place it somewhere else on the desk. I don't recommend this because it's too short.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great value for good quality medical shears
review: I purchased many for use in our medical kits (on ambulance). Good quality and easily cut through denim jeans.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Excellent quality product - impressed.
review: These work as well as my Littmann Classic II stethoscopes. EXTREMELY impressed with the value! Quality is excellent, very nice hard sided case, extra earpads, and a name tag. I purchased 3 and highly recommend them - you won't be disappointed.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Best over mitts
review: Nice to buy silicon oven mitts in a PAIR. good quality and keep hands cool. Good quality.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Didn't do a thing to speed up drain flow.
review: I used a snake prior to ensure no major blockages. Poured it all in and waited even longer than should be necessary. NO change at all in flow. I will remove the toilet and physically clear anything I find, as this was useless to me. Also note, this is a SMALL bottle - 1/2 gallon. Difficult to tell from picture.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Does NOT cover all my gray hair. Stains skin.
review: It doesn't work well on the grey around my temples. Also, it stains skin so be sure to apply a thin layer of vaseline around hairline and on ears.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: It's NOT EARRINGS - it is EARRING - SINGLE
review: I expected earrings, as per the heading. I didn't spend a lot of time looking for problems. I saw EARRINGS, liked the look and ordered them for my wife. ONE arrived. You can blame me for not taking more time to read the full description. Or you can look at the description in the heading, EARRINGS. Either way, it's just one (who sells ONE earring???)
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: SUPER THIN and began peeling off almost immediately
review: Cleaned the vehicle with Windex Surface Cleaner and allowed to dry. Applied the logos. Next morning when I called my wife out to take a look, 2 of the 3 logos were peeling up on one side. Combination of super thin vinyl and insufficient adhesive.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Immediately crashed
review: Apps NEVER crash on my LG5. Well, except for this one. It looks like a great game - I've been looking for a game just like this for years. I was pretty happy to find it. Then so disappointed when it wouldn't even open.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Excellent learning tool
review: I use this in my classroom to instruct the circulatory system, and CHF, CVD, etc. It is excellent quality Perfect for classroom instruction.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Looks great on the minivan
review: Went on easy and look great. Very pleased.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Works great to pre-heat the back of my ambulance.
review: I purchased this to help pre-heat the back of my ambulance (has 600w inverter and AC outlets). Works great to help quickly heat the back up. Has auto shut-off if tipped over. Would also be great for under a desk, etc.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: FANTASTIC! I've programmed 3 remotes with no issue at all.
review: Works EXACTLY as per the instructions. I programmed all 3 remotes within minutes. Best of all, when I bought my truck I was told by the dealer that it didn't come with remote locks. I proved her wrong! Not only did I discover I have remote locks, but I also have an alarm! Awesome!
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Does NOT moisturize! Leaves skin very dry - does NOT work!
review: This is the least effective moisturizer I've ever used. With slightly dry hands, after applying, my hands are dry within seconds to minutes. Neither my wife nor I would recommend this brand.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Look decent. Very small.
review: They look quite tiny on a safety helmet. Quality seems fine - I won't know unless I use the helmets outdoors which I hope not to have to do.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good for the price. Does NOT include the belt. Is not sewn well.
review: Very good deal for the price. Does not include the belt shown in pictures. Many loose threads, and the cross on the front is not sewn on at the edges - as much as an inch from the edge (uneven stitching, close to edge and far from edges). Large fit me with a thin shirt underneath - I am a 40" shoulder and slim-medium build.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Work just as expected. Programmed without issue.
review: They appear to be exactly as my OEM remotes. I programmed them without incident and they work great.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: It works.
review: Sadly, the ORIGINAL one I got with the humidifier was DOA out of the box. After a couple years of running the humidifier water constantly, I got this and had it installed. Worked as it should.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Big - Square - LEGO blocks do not adhere well - 2 sides are FAKE
review: Bricks only connect on sides. 2 sides are fakes. It's BIG! Obviously I got this for a kid - but it's WAY TOO BIG for a little kid. It's a fantastic concept, but a pretty crappy implementation.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: SUPERB! Does NOT get drowned out by strong radio stations
review: This is my 4th attempt to transmit satellite audio to my old factory stereo. The other transmitters I tried had static, and other stronger local radio stations were interfering. THIS transmitter however is POWERFUL! Even when there's a STRONG local radio signal, the audio from this transmitter is all I hear. ***** 5 stars!
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: I use it with a cheap blue tooth speaker over my bed headboard - great!
review: Very easy to connect - simply plug and play. I use it to transmit my TV audio to a bluetooth speaker on my headboard over my bed. Now we can watch TV without waking the kids on the other side of the wall behind the TV. Great sound quality too.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very nice animated stars - night light
review: It is a nice ceiling/wall projection effect light. Offers choice of colors for the stars, and a couple different star effects as well. It's decent quality. It would be nice with sharper images, or a focus lens. 4 out of 5
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very different from other headphones I've purchased. No ear 'cups'
review: Sits lightly on the head, and can be worn quite a bit longer than standard headphones with cups. The ear pads are soft, and sit over the ears but do not encase the ear. Sounds is good, looks good, and was very simple to pair.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Does NOT power 2x usb devices. NOT recommended.
review: All a lie. Does NOT power 2x devices at a time. Only 1 will work properly. I replaced my my Google Chromecast believing it was the problem. New one ALSO did not work at same time as splitter.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Look to be good quality. I added reflective stickers for added safety
review: Very inexpensive for quality safety hardhats. We needed two for our ambulance. It was a bit challenging figuring out how to install the head fittings in them, but once done it is quite secure and good quality. I added reflective stickers for identification and added night safety.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: FuN penlights! Come in 3 parts that are interchangeable
review: I took the pens apart when I put in the batteries, and switched the tops and bottoms for lots of multi-colored penlights. Our stall love them. The tops/bottoms screw on very easily as they are very well engineered. Great deal, very good packaging and shipping. I will definitely order again when we need more.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very realistic - we love them for live multicultural performances
review: These are fantastic - have a very realistic look. We use them in multicultural dance performances. From the audience, you really can't tell them apart from the real thing.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great set complete with case
review: These are perfect for a BLS/ ALS medical kit. Contains all sizes, secured in their own case - can toss in the kit and not worry about it.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Excellent price and ready to use out of the package.
review: This a complete set of NPAs, pre-lubricated and ready to use out of the package. Quality looks to be just as anticipated - perfect for in-ambulance use, BLS and ALS.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Excellent quality product - impressed.
review: The quality looks to be excellent. We are used to using an inferior product, and can appreciate the quality of this head immobilizer.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great buying experience. Good quality products.
review: This is yet another piece to complete my first aid kit. I am impressed with the quality and look forward to purchasing from this vendor again.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great solution that keeps kids/teens focused
review: Excellent solution for kids/ teens who want to play computer games when they should be doing their homework. Our kidsv schools use Google Cloud for homework.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great price and great quality.
review: Great rubber base mouse pad. It's much better than I expected for the price.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very nice.
review: We are adding feathers to it ourselves. They have a nice foam lining, and spacers to keep it away from your face.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: She loves it and gets compliments on it.
review: Looks great and protects my wife's phone.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: A must-have for any med kit
review: Easy to use and effective. I got enough to stock all my first aid kits with them.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: A light reading solution
review: Perfect solution for night reading.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great solution to having a temporary laundry line
review: It's great. I've used it and keep it on my deck. Works great.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very good, but warm
review: Very good but does get quite warm after a short time. Ibdo not think you will find any better.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Camera mount base is not set to 90 degrees, so the camera sits unlevel. See photo.
review: It iw not possible to set the angle to 90 degrees. It will just pop back into the wrong position. Difficult to see but the tripod is completely level, but the mount cannot be set level so camera sits crooked.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: NOT the game! This is a guide only! Scam
review: NOT the game! This is a guide only! Scam
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very good quality - only takes a drop or two in a diffuser to make the air smell fresh.
review: This is a good quality camphor essential oil. Unlike many other brands, this actually smells as it should, and it only takes a drop or two added to any other essential oil, to make the air feel clean and refreshing.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Nice idea - NOT durable. Ordered one for my son and one for myself - BOTH fell apart.
review: The design is great - holds everything I need to carry with me. Unfortunately, it's not durable. This was mine in the photo - stitching fell apart. My son just showed me his wallet yesterday, and an entire end peeled off of his. WHY can't people make things right? I would have paid more for a better product. NOTE - I ORIGINALLY rated this 5 stars! It WAS great until it fell apart. I knocked it down from 5 to 3, but when my son's ALSO fell apart, I reduced it again to 1 star.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Fits well and feels soft. It is a little too thin.
review: Very thin (semi-transparent). I'd rather a more durable sheet. Fits our king bed quite well.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Nice lanyard of the Philippines
review: OK quality. It's a nice lanyard representing the Philippines.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Cute outfit - looks just as pictured
review: The quality is as expected - quite thin material. But it does fit my wife as in the photo so I am happy with it.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: It's ok but I'm not really happy with it.
review: It's a big mouse - long. If you look, you will notice that it's about 1/2" longer than the typical gaming mouse. This presents a problem as the CLICK part of the mouse is very close to the end. So with normal hand placement, clicking the mouse simply does nothing. You have to move your hand forward to reach the actual (working) mouse buttons.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good quality, compact remote control.
review: Worked flawlessly. Good range. Looks to be good quality - has some weight to it.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Solid plastic watch case, date too small to read even with READING GLASSES!
review: This is NOTHING like any Casio I've ever seen. It's a solid piece of plastic and I cannot read the date even with reading GLASSES ON! Very tiny! Nothing moves - the outer dial is fake, as it's just a solid plastic case with no moving parts.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Pretty good but not great.
review: It's a pretty decent battery, however it doesn't hold a great charge. It dies rather quickly. Within a couple of hours of usage, I need to connect the phone to a charger.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Decent quality and works great.
review: Worked perfectly and is now a part of my gig kit.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Watered down weak scent. Not recommended.
review: Not pure. Weak scent and takes far too much to produce aroma. Not at all worth it.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: As good as others made it out to be. Very happy with it.
review: The others didn't exaggerate. It is well designed and pretty comfortable for an average size man. Notice the feet are not just caps - they are designed to be sturdy on different ground. Also, orange is my favorite color.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great value for very good Powerpoint remote.
review: Works as hoped. great value for the price and does just what I had expected.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: It's a quality (SAM) splint at a great price.
review: It's a quality (SAM) splint at a great price. It's perfect for my First Responder medical kit.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Received WRONG product. Still awaiting replacement.
review:
Sent me wrong items. Also had leaking bottles inside (oily in the box). I of course did not want all of these tiny bottles. I would be happy with just ylang ylang and bergamot for the 60ml, or some other flowery scents added.

I do hope one day to receive a replacement for the incorrect order.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Hollow bottoms and very light. Look very nice.
review: Hollow bottoms. Pictures and description do not say the bottom is hollow. The result is the tumblers are very light. I made the purchase with the belief they would have some weight to them, but with the hollow bottoms, they are too light. They do look very much like glass, so the appearance is nice. However this is not what I was looking for.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: ROKU is great - easiest way to turn a TV into a SMART TV.
review: I love ROKU. Have one stick in the house and one box (with headphone jack in remote), and also purchased 2x ROKUs for my parents' tvs. Simplest way to turn a tv into a smart tv.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Damaged my phone. Seriously overheats phone.
review: WARNING! Significantly OVERHEATS phone! Causes screen burnin from heat, and also problems restarting and shutting down phone. My power button STOPPED working, and only after removing the Bear and waiting fornthe phone to cool would it reboot. NOT recommended. You've been warned.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Love these super white, super bright interior lights.
review: I've only used 2 so far for interior lights (bottom of rear view mirror). LOVE it! Super bright white light that fills my car. I do not have interior lights in the backseat of my car, and was hoping these lights would light up more of the interior including the back seat. I am NOT disappointed! Excellent lighting that helps light up the whole interior.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: VERY GOOD extended battery for LG4. I wish they made this for the LG5, but sadly it's not offered.
review: My wife NEVER has any issue with her battery since getting this extended battery. The case is good quality as well. I've noticed a friend of mine also has the same one and loves his too.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: HIgh quality - stiff cable.
review: Very good quality. Quite stiff, so only purchase if you don't need a flexible cable. Easily crimps if not careful.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good but not great.
review: Compresses almost all the way when placed between legs/ knees. Could be improved with denser foam in center. While not cooling, it does not seem to add to body heat.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very nice and high quality
review: High quality and lights up very well. I feel much better when I know my kids are wearing this when they have to be out at night.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very nice quality case.
review: A gift for my son - he loves the pop out stand feature. I like the belt clip/case.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: BETTER than you'd expect. Truly plug n play - works through walls.
review: Was a gift for someone. Plugged into her MAC and it instantly worked. Also worked through 2 walls.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good product - fit well and looks as good as the original.
review: Works well. Installed easily and looks as good as the original.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Just as we hoped - very nice.
review: Chef loves it and it matches his black jacket nicely.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Leaves layer of gray underneath. Only good for very short hair. Not good for normal short hair (above ears and collar).
review: Cleans hair very well. Keeps hair dark, HOWEVER, only on the outer layer. Lift up your hair and you see gray - VERY noticeable. This product is ONLY suitable if you have very short hair. Then it's a 5 out of 5. For normal short hair (above the ears and above the collar), it's a 3.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Fantastic service and product at an exceptional price
review: Very, very happy to see classics being offered at exceptional prices. Two thumbs up for Amazon.ca !
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: High quality construction, great sound card,
review: Great to carry in my DJ gig bag. I've used it may times and it works great every time. Good quality - very well made, and very inexpensive for the quality.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Relaxing and even sleeping comes easy with this wonderful app. A must-have for me.
review: Thank the heavens for this program. It's helped me relax and fall asleep with SOOOO much customization. Next to the alarm app, this is the one I can't do without.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Activation issues. Static in earplugs new right out of the box.
review: Took many attempts to activate over WIRED network connection. Activated 1st time when I changed it to wireless. LOTS of static in the headphones brand new right out of the box. Moving the connector around produces static sound in headphones as well. I will try my own headphones and see if it's any better. But for the price difference, it should have better headphones.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Love it - SMALLER than expected (smaller than Rubic's Cube), but super fast and smooth
review: My son loves it! Fastest, smoothest Rubic's Cube he's ever seen. The blocks are a blur when he's using it.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very nice quality and work great
review: My 4 boys really like these. They are solid wood with nice rubber ends. Perfectly balanced, so they roll nicely and can even end up landing on the ends.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great quality and perfect for most snow conditions
review: I love Bolle products. The pink lens is great for pretty much any snow conditions.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Poor quality but will do the job fine
review: Sound quality is barely passable. Comes DISASSEMBLED - you must assemble yourself (very easy to do). Box is ok for storing the stethoscope. Quality is very poor and it's pretty flimsy. But as it doesn't take long to teach someone how to read BP, it will hold up fine for many uses.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good but overpriced.
review: Good quality, but overpriced. Installation - use - quality is no better than the $12 Trond AC2
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Seem very nice, but not reliably charging up on our devices.
review: I think every one of them has failed now. Not sure why, they just aren't charging our devices.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great containers - see inside, keeps things safe and dry.
review: I use these in my medical kit to hold different bandaids. Excellent product - highly recommended for any medic's kit.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Must-have for heavy bags - reduced shoulder fatigue. Not anti-slip.
review: Makes a huge difference - much less shoulder fatigue than with a stock shoulder belt/pad. A nice addition to the design would be to add anti-slip.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good quality product that fits nice on the belt.
review: Quite a nice product. takes up very little space on the belt.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good performance at a good price.
review: Nice video cards. A little annoying to select and use the correct size/ shape mounting bracket.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Quite the game - everyone chickened out too soon
review: Too many gross ones. Maybe I just had bad luck. Sour milk is soooo disgusting. Sadly, everyone chickened out far too soon when we played it.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great deal for quality batteries. I've used two so far and they work perfectly.
review: A whole lot of batteries at a great price. Nicely packaged. I've used just two so far, but they work perfectly.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: The perfect lunch container.
review: Fantastic for lunches. But also for my wife's earrings, necklaces, etc. She liked them so much that she started using them for her jewelry, lol. Now I need to order more because they are just perfect.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Beautiful flags
review: I ordered 2 of these 2 packs - beautiful flags. We used them in the Canada Day Parade and the crowd loved them, especially the Canada 150 flag. Can't wait to order the Canada 151 version :)
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good quality little first aid kit.
review: Good quality little first aid kit. Can't beat the price.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Top flap is too short, side flaps do not fold in properly, and the shoulder strap pad is too smooth and slippery.
review: Shoulder strap is SLIPPERY. It's a smooth plastic shoulder pad that slips right off the shoulder. Also the small side flaps are designed awkward so they don't fold in properly under the main flap. And the top flap is much too short. With a normal amount of first aid materials, the top flap leaves about 4 inches UNCOVERED material in the front pockets.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good quality individually packaged emesis bags
review: Individually packaged emesis bags. Good quality and perfect for my medical kit.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Bright, colourful flags of decent quality for the price
review: Nice quality fabric flags. Very good deal with nice bright colours. We use them for multicultural events.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Exceptional customer service and feature-filled quality products
review: The radios are great, and the battery is just what I needed to replace a defective one. The company is fantastic to deal with - top notch! When I had an issue, they immediately responded and took action to remedy the problem. ALL electronics have the possibility of having a defect. What is important is there is minimal chance, and when there is a problem, the company stands behind their products. Retevis does, and I give them a 5 star rating for product quality, suitability, features, and especially for exceptional customer service.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Has the right tips, but tips don't fit snug into the screwdriver.
review: It has all the specialty tips I need, but the tips don't fit snugly into the screwdriver. It does not tighten up enough to gold the tip in place, so when I apply the tip to a screw, the tip sinks half way inside of the screwdriver. I would recommend this set because it has the tips I needed and I couldn't find any other comparable products.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Too bulky and thick for my use. Good quality, but wasn't what I expected from seeing the photos.
review: The quality is decent, but it's much thicker than it appears. I find it too bulky to use, so it's now sitting in a drawer.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Works perfectly - good shipping
review: This battery worked exactly as we had hoped, and expected. Simply to replace, and fixes the problem we had with a bad battery that would not charge.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Worst product on Amazon - we could not communicate with my son for 3 weeks while he was away at camp
review:
This is the worst product I have ever ordered online. Very difficult to activate on their website, and very difficult to configure to work properly on a cellular network. It consistently connected to the worst cell provider and signal available, until I forced it to connect to my preferred network. It works very intermittently at best (really barely ever works), and when it did work, it would drop the connection/ disconnect from the network repeatedly. The amount of data usage permitted was exceeded to my bewilderment. HOW is it possible to use up 40MB of data on FB Messenger? 1 character is 1 byte, 1023 characters is 1 KB, and 1 MB is 1 MILLION bytes (characters). But it ran out within a few days and gave the message, "USAGE IS THROTTLED UNTIL the 1st of NEXT MONTH".

This is seriously the WORST product on Amazon in my opinion.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very powdery and does not adhere. Comes off very easily. Difficult to apply. Very long delivery time.
review: Very, very long time to arrive. Powder comes off far too easily - VERY powdery and does not stick. Also very difficult to apply. Frankly, it was a waste of money and my wife doesn't even use it. Seriously very disappointing product.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great quality on par with Kenwood and Motorola
review: Great quality that is on par with Kenwood and Motorola professional series handheld remote radios. The cable has a good quality rubber feel to it, as opposed to being hard and inflexible. I expect it would work with any pro-series radio as it appears to be just like the Motorolas and Kenwoods I use.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Exceeds expectations - beautiful shoe.
review: Beautiful patent leather shoes. I can't say for certain that it's leather, but time will tell. I love the pattern within the patent leather toes - looks very sharp. Far better looking than the picture - you will definitely be pleasantly surprised, even after reading my review. It will exceed your expectations.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good quality professional quality product
review: Perfect for my med kit. It's decent quality and should it ever be needed, I know I can rely upon it's quality.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great belt but not-so-great belt attachments
review: Whatever physical shape it arrives in is how it remains. Although it is flexible, it has a memory and returns to it's form. I use the long open top slotted one for my eyeglasses. Unfortunately my glasses get caught on something inside - a seam or crease or something. The belt is excellent - I love it. It has a bit of lumbar support in the back so that was a very nice bonus. I'd recommend the belt and a couple of the attachments, but much of the attachments will result in frustration.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Fantastic tool - contributed to passing my EMR scenario!
review: I love my Raptor. Funny thing, on my EMR practical scenario (exam), I needed to make a 3-sided occlusion bandage. I was scrambling to find the shears in the bag but couldn't find it, then I remembered my Raptor clipped on my belt. I used it to cut up a baggie, and then I used it again to open up the oxygen tank regulator. You will love it.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Exceeds expectations - on-par with Kenwood and Motorola professional series
review: I am used to using Kenwood and Motorola professional 2-way radios. The things I expect from a professional quality radio are found in the Retrevis radios. Fully programmable, quality belt clip, quality handsets and great reception, rechargeable batteries, multi-colored display options. And they can even be programmed to connect to low-end radios such as those cheap ones that BEEP when you call another radio. FAR better quality, more options and better performance than I expected.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great for students
review: Chances are you are used to going through a lot of these. This is a reasonably priced LED penlight for students, or as a spare in your kit.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Exceptional with one drawback - leaves small gap on 3 edges
review: This would be an absolutely exceptional product, but the glass leaves a gap of about 1mm on the left, top and right sides. If it was just a little wider and taller, it would protect the entire screen. It comes very nicely packaged, in a plastic case inside the cardboard slotted box. It could not be easier to apply. Simply open packet 1 (alcohol) and wipe the screen. Open packet 2 (towelette) to dry the screen. Then carefully position the glass over the phone screen, lower it and touch the center of the glass to the screen. It removes all the air itself - absolutely perfect application.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good quality
review: I like the quality of the cables, and they come neatly packaged in a box with individual slots for each cable.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: A good quality cape suitable for hair salon use (but I use at home)
review: Good quality replacement that is suitable for a hair salon (but I use at home).
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very good quality gloves suitable for SAR (search and rescue)
review: Good quality gloves for search and rescue or any security job.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: OEM batteries that arrived with a charge and ready to use. They charge to full with no problems.
review: No complaints - arrived quickly, packaged well, and charge fully without any issues.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good quality product that is as good as other reviews say!
review: Ooh this really hits the spot! Gives a great neck massage, and also works well on legs, arms, etc.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great pulse oximer that includes a nice belt carry case and carry strap.
review: Loaded with features - I really didn't expect it to do a much as it does, and so well. Very bright and clear display. Gives me all the info I could ask for in a pulse oximeter.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Fits Acer Liquid Zest phone perfectly. Looks good and works well.
review: The phone fits perfectly. Works well for my needs, and it's very reasonably priced.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Tricky to use, but I feel safe using it to allow my lovebird outdoors
review: Very tricky to get on and off my lovebird, but she loves being outside.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good quality device that should be in every real first aid/ responder kit.
review: Very easy to use, excellent quality, and compact. I hope I never, 'need' it, but if I do, I am confident it will do its job well.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: It may not be the best name in the industry, but it does its job very well.
review: Does what it says it should. Very cost efficient (good bang for the buck). Very noticeable difference over using an active system with built-in dsp.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Best energy drink on the market. I love it.
review: The ONLY energy drink that doesn't taste like medicine. Tastes like REAL blueberry juice, and isn't nearly acidic as other drinks. Loaded with vitamins (D complex), and best of all, it's sweetened with cane sugar - no some chemical additive. This is my favorite energy drink and flavour.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Most EMR courses include this book (USA) or Canadian Red Cross EMR book. These are far better than just a regular textbook
review: Very well written and easy to follow along. Includes access to AUDIOBOOK to follow along with the book, as well as access to test questions and additional online videos and information.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Personal preference.
review: It's OK but not the order I like it to be.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Clear fonts used, and concise information - useful job aid.
review: Clear and concise. Handy to have when you need to quickly determine where an injury may lie.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Handy pocket job-aid
review: Contains a lot of useful reference information. It doesn't have everything I'd like it to have, but it does have most BLS information presented in a handy format.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great tool - Look for latest version.
review: Perfect for a nurse or advanced first aider (paramedic, etc.)
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very nice handy TAC tool to have
review: Great weight and balance to it. Easily adapts for different needs. Mine came without the flint (fire starter), but aside from that, it's pretty impressive. I did also receive a velvet carrying pouch that the tool slips into for storing.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Stopped working. Crown does nothing. Just junk. Warranty refunding due to defects.
review: Completely failed. Hands stopped moving. Crown does NOTHING to the hands and just spins. Returned for warranty repair and informed I will receive a refund due to defects. Absolute garbage.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Indispensable but some errors
review: Very helpful and very much appreciated. Some small spelling/ grammatical errors that can be overlooked. Medicine #67 is DANGEROUSLY WRONG. Do NOT remove an object impaled in the eye - SECURE it.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: One of the best choices for a wireless router - perfect for Second Life players
review: EXCELLENT wireless router with all the bells and whistles.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Not a quality product, but I knew that before buying it.
review: I knew what I was buying and expected it to be what it was. These have a short lifespan, due to the fact the plastic quickly wears away where it tightens, making it pretty much useless after some 20-40 uses.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good but drips.
review: Good, but I don't like that it leaves a puddle when used for any period of time. It would be 5 stars if it either didn't drip, or had a drip catch tray.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very high quality balanced cables with metal ends.
review: Very high quality cable with metal ends. My sound equipment is top of the line pro-series and tour series, and I will only use professional quality cables, which these are.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: FAST-PACED arcade style
review: Even though there are two modes, 'arcade' and 'timed', they are both really what are known as, 'arcade' style. I love puzzle games where intellect plays some part, but this isn't a game that tests your ability to think of solutions, it is purely a fast-action paced game of reaction. Not for me... I should have tried the demo first.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: My kids LOVE this game and play it far more than I'd like them to
review: My kids love this game - they play it more than I'd like them to... it's that good.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Works fine but the design leaves something to be desired
review: Rather awkward design on the right side (for a right-handed person). My little finger just isn't comfortable because there's not enough room for my finger to rest on the edge, and it's 1/2 on - 1/2 off the mouse.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Excellent product - simple plug n' play with Windows 10
review: This works exactly like I had hoped it would. Simply plug n' play with my Windows 10 laptop. Perfect sound - excellent product.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good but one is visibly slightly larger than the other.
review: One shoe is slightly larger than the other, as if it had been tried on and returned. The quality is very good and I am otherwise satisfied. But I am not so happy with one shoe being visibly larger than the other. Quality control issue? Returned shoe? I don't know...
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Excellent quality and lighting
review: I am very pleased with these bulbs. The light they produce is truly daylight color, and very bright. But what impressed me about these bulbs is that the LEDs produce a single white light and not 5 individual spots of white light. I am replacing other LEDs from another company, and the old ones with 3 LEDs had distinctive beams of light, whereas these ones blend together to provide a much nicer result. I highly recommend these bulbs based on my experience.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Misleading and over exaggerated features, and inability to CUE through headphones makes this a very poor choice
review:
Cannot separate USB channels into left and right in monitor or headphones. You CANNOT cue or listen to one channel without listening to BOTH channels at the same time. So this mixer becomes USELESS as a USB mixer, because you MUST use 2x channels on your mixer to separate the signal you send to the headphones. That means NOT using the USB connection at all for mixing, but instead using sound out from your computer.

To be able to cue a left or right channel, all Behringer needed to do was to add BALANCE to the headphones so you could listen to the left or right channel. But they were too cheap to add a simple switch to make it possible.

It's likely pretty easy to modify it yourself, but why bother when there are other mixers that do it for you.

Also, while Behringer does make a feedback eliminator, this mixer does NOT handle feedback elimination. It simply has an LED in the EQ levels, and if the signal is stronger, you see the red LED glow. If you wanted to adjust your EQ on the mixer to deal with the problem, you would have to affect MANY frequencies at the same time. And if you wanted to connect an external EQ, say 24-32-64 channel for example, then the EQ would be AFTER the mixer, in which case the LEDs would not be affected.

Also, the mic preamps SUCK! They are nowhere near professional quality - they are very poor quality and unsuitable for professional use. Fine for an amateur DJ, but nowhere near the quality you'd want for use with a professional sound system, including a band.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Unreliable - they fail to tighten within a short timeframe - plastic wears through and clamp cannot remain closed
review: Here's the issue, and it's a BIG ISSUE! The metal thumbscrew tightens up into PLASTIC. The plastic is soft, and within no time at all, the thumbscrew will tighten THROUGH the plastic and it will simply not lock. The result is that your effect light will NOT be secured to the truss/ t-bar, and creates a very serious liability issue! I was using Chauvet clamps and switched to ADJ because Chauvet has round thumbscrews whereas ADJ has this wider type that is easier to tighten. Unfortunately these ADJ clamps are NOT reliable - I recommend against using them for safety reasons.

review_title: Great video card that fixed my Windows 10 freezing/ crashing issue
review:
Very happy with this card. Short story, my mother's Windows 10 computer had issues that were 100% fixed by installing an EVGA GTX 950. So when my dad's Windows 10 computer (different make/model of computer) was doing the same thing, I checked the event logs and saw there were video issues as well. I bought this card and installed it (ANYONE can install it - has printed instructions and it's super easy). After that, his computer was also fixed.

Both computers were ALWAYS crashing, like every few minutes they would freeze. My mom's wouldn't even start up anymore. But after installing these cards, they are both 100% fixed with NO freezing problems whatsoever.

I highly recommend EVGA video cards, and this one especially.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: 100% fixed my Windows 10 BSOD crashing/ freezing problem
review: Very happy with this card. My mother's computer (Windows 10) was crashing ALL THE TIME! Literally, all the time - wouldn't stay on for more than a few minutes. I spent a lot of money trying to diagnose the problem, and I updated all of the device drivers, but nothing would prevent it from freezing. But as soon as I installed this card the computer was fixed - no more crashing.

review_title: VERY healthy (contains turmeric), VERY tasty!!! and smells really good too
review:
Oh, this curry mix is really, really good! It smells great and it livens up the taste of everything I put it on from pizza to soups, rice, and curry dishes that we make with coconut milk and canned green curry - just add lots of this spice and it makes it the most incredible curried chicken dish ever.

I bought it for the turmeric. I called Club House and asked the ingredients, and when I found it had a lot of turmeric, I decided to order it. In India, Sri Lanka and other Asian countries, turmeric is actually prescribed by doctors to treat intestinal problems. As I have Crohn's Disease, I thought I'd give the natural treatment a try. I can personally say that I am feeling better and believe there is an improvement. I will continue to use this and the pure turmeric I also ordered, and hopefully I will get a lot better as a result.

review_title: Very entertaining for word game fanatics
review: Although I got this as a free app of the day, had I known of it beforehand, I would certainly have purchased it. I enjoy word games, and this one offers great variety in game play. A great addition to any game collection.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Mind expanding
review: Thinking outside the box is the key to solving the very fun puzzles. And as the levels get more challenging, it leaves the player feeling a greater sense of accomplishment when they complete them. I give it 5 stars for being simple to play, bug free, and challenging.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: 1 Star is generous. Incredibly short game is made long by puzzles that make no sense. I
review: Save yourself from the aggrevation! Thisn't what I would refer to as a game, because all you do is click on every pixel on the screen in hopes of being able to interract with something. IMO it shouldn't even be in the store.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Does not see shared printers on remote local usb
review: I have an external NAS storage device with USB printer connected. I can print with HP remote print app, but this app does not even see it. I am connected to a WiFi network with the NAS, however this app sees the NAS on a different hotspot SSID that is also connected to the same router with RJ45 cable. It should instead be seeing the NAS on the WiFi network the tablet is connected to, but doesn't.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: One of my favorite escape games
review: Excellent graphics, creative thinking behind the puzzle design, and help a click away. I enjoyed it more than other escape games I've played.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Images and ads... nothing more
review:
This is a collection of images that can be used for backgrounds. No options at all - zero. Ads at the bottom.
I honestly don't see any value whatsoever in installing this, and I fail to even see how it is an app as it doesn't have any settings nor capabilities.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Very fun to play, but progress gets lost
review: The game is about building, purchasing and managing businesses and a community. It is goal based; if you don't raise enough money in the given time period, you lose and all progress is lost... you lose the town you built. For 5his reason, it has very limited replay appeal, and leaves the player disappointed. If you enjoy the challenge and not so much the progress of developing your own town, it's a great game choice.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Too easy and FORCED to review
review: Puzzles are so far mucn too easy. There doesn't appear to be any intelligemce to the game, in so much as increasing difficulty. Each puzzle is as simple as the one preceding it. And forced reviews annoy me. I said NO when asked, but after each level it asks me again to rate.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Good app but SKIP the INTRO!!!
review:
The into is the publisher's view, and not the view shared with the church, nor the Vatican.

The Book of Enoch has been dated and verified. The text of Jude 1:14 is identical to that found in the Book of Enoch found in the Dead Sea Scrolls. It has been dated to 200 BC. It foretells of the Mmessiah's coming, being the Son of God, AND sacrificing his blood for man. I can't speak for the other books, but Pope Benedict XVI included reference to the (recovered) Book of Enoch in an Easter homily. Read it and decide for yourself.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Cannot resize text and ads
review: Is it really FREE if you are forced to view ads? This app has NO functionality whatsoever. No search, no text options or ANY options for that matter. Cannot register, nor is there any option to remove ads. It appears to all be there, so I rated it a 2. But as I can't resize text to read it, I can't rate any higher than 2.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Excellent concept close to perfection
review:
Never ending challenging immersive fun! It just needs minor fixes.

Please allow option for EDGE FLASH for collisions, and option to DISABLE vibration (vibration makes unwanted noise).
Some of the rings are too short to go through (intentional?) Night version would be cool, where ball glows and lights up area around it.

This app has exponential potential. Please keep us updated as it is further developed.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: This is NOT an app - Website POSING as app
review:
This is just an URL redirector wi5h POPUP ads. Go direct with your browser and avoid the ads. 16personalities dot com/free-personality-test

It should be removed from the app store as it sets a bad precedent. The fake app was made using AppsGeyser - make any website an app.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Advert supported app. Fragmented info about DJs
review:
This is a very simple list of DJs. When you tap a name, it opens up a page and displays a 'tidbit' of about a paragragh with basic information about the respective DJ. I clicked for the next tip, and it repeated after just a couple tips.

Mmuch more information available on WIKI

review_title: Not as described. No tests.. No DiSC
review: Complete waste of time. First, it is NOT an english app, second, it only links to their website, and third, it has nothing to do with DiSC. Uninstalled.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Other reviews are unfair
review: My young boys and I love this game. It's incredibly simplistic to play - simply pull back an imaginary slingshot, take aim and release. Your chimp flies through the air, grabbing diamonds and bananas along the way. Get all the diamonds to get the best score. Graphics are awesome, characters adorable, and sou d perfectly matched with gameplay. This is one of the best games for Android.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: My son LOVES this game!
review: My son LOVES this game! I have more than 60 games for my Android tablet, but out of all of them, this is by far his favorite. To me it looks boring, but then again, I've not played it. My son on the other hand has played it a lot and really enjoys the game. I'd definitely recommend it and give it 5 stars for entertainment value based on my son's love for the game.

review_title: Useless and unpolished app

review_title: Nothing New
review: I don't see anything new. In fact, I think it has less than the actual pixel dungeon.

review_title: Good but could be improved
review:
Graphics (card faces) are actually blurry on an 8" tablet screen. Can't see score during gameplay, as it only shows after a game ends. Computer opponent is stupid; with one card left it intentionally changes suit to something OTHER than what the suit of the last card is. Also, no options to change grapchi environment (Only one standard cardface, no card backs, no table options). No music, etc.

But it is nevertheless a fun game.

review_title: They are NOT BLACK ink - they were all blue ink!
review: There are many reviews, and the one voted MOST USEFUL was not useful at all! My wife can ONLY use black ink, and the pens we received are ALL BLUE ink. The color of the ink SHOULD be included in the description, as it would have saved me time and money, and I would not have ended up disappointing my wife :(

review: The Hosa 'PRO' audio product line is good quality, and should last for years. While the Hosa products are generally of a low quality, the pro line uses a much thicker shielded cable, and metal connectors.

Looked very promising but every game starts again at level 1.
The controls for left-right do not extend to the sides of the screen, so I repeatedly missed pressing the direction control button.

Has potential but seems like a trial version.

review_title: So far not impressed
review: Free app that requires coins to play. That's like saying you can go swimming, but you can't get wet. It is unpleasant to be required to do tricks in order to play.
