review_title: Worth less than free IMO
review: I do not like Facebook or online reliant games. I don't want to play a word game in a competitive room with strangers, nor do I wish to play it with FB friends. Immediately uninstalled.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Tiny thumbnail - No photos
review: The tiny thumbnail image in the app description is what you get in the app. There are NO PHOTOS, only thumbnails. The information is what you can find on the web. Nice compilation, but no full size images to help bring the data into perspective. Basically what appearw to be an app churned out of a mill.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Paid version plagued with popup ads
review: I paid but still have ads. I uninstalled then reinstalled but it still has the ads. I don't like ads.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Insight into a very strange mind... too difficult to relate to
review: I appreciate this mother and father sharing the story of their little Angel and their personal journey in accepting his passing. Although I am a parent going through the passing of our baby, I am unable to relate to the experience of the author. The experiences shared are very bizarre... really out there. While I do understand it is a personal journey, it is one that is extremely unlikely to be similar in any way to other parents suffering the loss of their baby. I tried - really I did. But the story doesn't seem to follow a chronological order and there are too many gaps between experiences and groups of thoughts. Again though, it is kind of them to share their story, even if it isn't something that I could relate to.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Weak... have to remove and search every time
review:
I use this with Windows 8 Professional 64 bit. It installed very easily. The problem is that first, it is quite weak and often doesn't find the bluetooth device a foot away. The other problem is that it does NOT automatically reconnect to my powered bluetooth speaker. I have to REMOVE the speaker from the list of detected devices, then search again and connect.

I use the speaker with my smartphone, and what my smartphone does that this does not is:
1. Allows me to rename the connection from A33 to TDK Speakers
2. Automatically connects when I turn on bluetooth on my smartphone
3. Easily detect and use bluetooth devices without having to REMOVE the device, then search for it again and connect again.

Maybe all bluetooth adapters for Windows 8 are this lame... I don't know as this is the only one I have. But compared to the one built into my smartphone, I am very unimpressed with this one.

Once it is connected, it works, BUT it's very easy to accidentally disconnect then have to waste time trying to get it working again.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: The right part for my Fluval 304
review:
It's tricky trying to get the right part for a Fluval 304 as there are two different models. One model uses the ceramic part that has a yellow plastic holder, but another model of the 304 uses the same as the 305. Fluval website does not show the model that uses the same parts as the 305.

How to tell the difference:
If your Fluval 304 uses the straight impeller blades, then you need THIS part to work with the ceramic shaft.

If your Fluval 3-4 uses the curved impeller blades, then you need the CLEAR cover and NOT this one.

Mine uses the straight impeller blades, and this is the correct cover (smoke color). I had the clear cover (it broke twice because it was the wrong one).
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Lies. Regular price is the sale price, NOT $65 as it states.
review:
First, Van Houtte coffees are not very strong as compared to Timothys and Green Mountain. There is an after taste with this brand as well, so I avoid it except for Irish Cream.

Second, the regular price is NOT $65 as it states, it is always under $20. See Keurig website and see for yourself. This is supposed to be a sale, but it's more of a scam to trick people into believing it's some awesome deal that it isn't.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: Great little tool for the price
review: If it had battery backup it would be a 5. But it is really useful for ensuring you aren't close to tripping the breaker with too big of a load.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com

review_title: INCREDIBLE sound! Blows the $300 Sony out of the water!
review:
As a professional full-time DJ, I appreciate good clean, crisp sound and punchy bass. I was trying out many of the Bluetooth speakers at Best Buy and then at The Source (Radio Shack). When I saw this model on sale, I thought I'd test it out. Well I was BLOWN AWAY by the quality for the price! Sounds awesome - loud, good bass, and very crisp sound.

Easy to connect with Bluetooth, and also works as a speaker phone with your smart phone. Also has Aux. input.

Rechargeable lithium battery that lasts 6 hours or so, and also has a USB output for charging your cell phone, etc. whenever it is plugged in.

I LOVE this unit and highly recommend it! Stop by The Source or anywhere else they carry it, and compare it to the Sony, etc. I'm certain you will find it to be a pleasant surprise.
author: MulticulturalFirstAid com
